{
  "bead_id": "B-fabf2d0f",
  "title": "Wrap run_once in quiescence loop with progress markers",
  "agent_type": "developer",
  "description": "Modify `command_run` in `src/agent_takt/cli/commands/run.py` to wrap the single `scheduler.run_once()` call (currently lines 119\u2013135) in a `while True:` loop that exits when `not result.started`. Use `args.max_cycles` as a safety cap: break with a `console.warn(...)` when the cycle index reaches the cap (skip the cap when `args.max_cycles <= 0`). Emit a `console.info(f'Cycle {cycle_index}')` marker before each iteration when `cycle_index > 1` (preserves backward-compatible single-cycle output). The accumulator dicts (`started`, `completed`, `blocked`, `correctives_created`) and `deferred_count` continue to aggregate across all cycles unchanged. The `reporter.stop()` call stays in the `finally` block outside the loop.",
  "status": "in_progress",
  "bead_type": "task",
  "parent_id": "B-53425f62",
  "dependencies": [
    "B-f1ec0e51"
  ],
  "acceptance_criteria": [
    "`command_run` contains a `while True:` loop that calls `scheduler.run_once()` on every iteration.",
    "Loop exits via `break` when `not result.started`.",
    "Loop also breaks when `cycle_index >= args.max_cycles` (for `max_cycles > 0`) and emits a console warning.",
    "A `console.info(f'Cycle {cycle_index}')` line is emitted for cycle 2 and beyond (cycle 1 is silent).",
    "`reporter.stop()` is called in a `finally` block wrapping the entire loop.",
    "Accumulator dicts merge results from all cycles correctly.",
    "No changes to scheduler/core.py."
  ],
